I bought this Springfield XD9 Mod. 2 Sub Compact 9mm new last year. I took it out to the gun range the first weekend I owned it and put 150 total rounds of factory 115 grain FMJ regular and hollow point ammo through it with absolutely no issues.   It was bought to serve as my home protection gun with its compact size and high capacity, so I haven't shot it much other than to take it out periodically to ensure it is working well and that I can shoot it with accuracy. Last weekend I put the 500th round through it and it shoots and works as well as the first 150 rounds did.   I hadn't planned on selling this gun (I always have good intentions...) but this is my only 9mm semi-automatic pistol and have decided to get down to just my revolvers for now. I may buy another 9mm next year, but for now I will be a .38 caliber shooter.   This Springfield XD9 Mod. 2 Sub Compact 9mm is a great shooting and feeling gun with a nice trigger. title: For Sale:  ATN PS22-3 Night Vision Sight W/ IR Illuminator
postcontent: ATN PS22-3 Night Vision Sight W/ IR Illuminator.The ATN PS22 is an attachment for a Daytime Riflescopes with 1x Magnification that converts a scope into a high-quality night vision weapon sight. The ATN PS22 System mounts in front of a Daytime Scope. Re-zeroing of the scope is not required. The ATN PS22 comes standard with 7/8" weaver mount. The IR Illuminator can be mounted onto the optional Picatinny Rail. This ingenious setup allows the shooter to go from day to night in less than 30 seconds without tools, without changes in eye relief and remain zeroed all around the clock. The ATN PS22 is a complex optical-electronic system. The device contains an image intensifier tube assembly with an integrated high-voltage power source and three volt battery housing.    A night vision device works by taking existing light, whether infra-red, moonlight or starlight, and changing it into visible light. This visible light is amplified to the point where it may be viewed in the device's eyepiece. The process, where the existing light (made up of photons) moves through a photocathode tube, changes to electrons that are electro-chemically amplified and then driven against a phosphorus screen to return them to visible light, gives the final image a green hue.Technical Information Total Darkness IR System: Yes Generation: 3Resolution: 64-72 lp/mm Magnification: 1xProshield Lens Coating: Yes Range of Focus: 10m to infinity Controls: Direct Automatic Brightness Control: Yes Bright Light Cut-off: Yes Infrared Illuminator: Detachable IR450 IR Indicator: Yes Low Battery Indicator: No Power Supply: 1 CR123A Battery Life: 60 hrs Environmental Rating: Waterproof Operating Temperature: -40 to +50 °C Dimensions: 5.9"x3.2"x2.8"Weight: 1.4 lbs      ATN PS22-3 Weapon Site IR450 IR Illuminator Lens Caps Light Suppressor Adjustment Wrench (2) Adapters (Scope Mounting System)  Remote Control Switch User's Manual Carrying Case.
